furicam2 (2.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Noise Reduction and Edge Enhancement are now Off / Fast / Quality
    selectors (default Quality), replacing the on/off toggles: HIGH_QUALITY
    on stills, FAST on the preview/video stream.
  * Face capture mode (FACE_PRIORITY scene with face detection).
  * "Reset Settings to Defaults" button at the bottom of the settings panel.
  * Recommended-default markers: a gold star on the recommended option of
    each selector (with a legend) and a gold tick at every slider's default
    position; the resolution pickers star the highest resolution and note
    that the 4:3 aspect ratio has the widest field of view.
  * Gallery: recognise .mp4 recordings (not only legacy .mkv) and refresh
    after a recording finishes, matching photo behaviour.
  * Gallery: sort by modification time so the newest capture is shown first
    (the previous name sort wrongly surfaced an old legacy-named photo).
  * Gallery: video thumbnails are extracted with ffmpeg (fixes the black
    thumbnail from the YUV/hardware-decode frame path) and shown in the
    review button in video mode.  Adds an ffmpeg runtime dependency.

 -- Sean Pollard <spollard08@gmail.com>  Mon, 22 Jun 2026 09:21:24 -0400

furicam2 (2.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * RAW (DNG) capture: a colour-accurate dual-illuminant DNG saved beside each
    JPEG (dependency-free writer; sensor white/black levels + colour matrices).
  * Noise reduction and edge enhancement toggles (HIGH_QUALITY on stills).
  * Tone Map selector (Standard / HDR / Contrast): a real in-ISP dynamic-range
    optimisation via a custom tone curve (HDR lifts shadows + rolls off
    highlights; Contrast is punchier) on the live preview and capture, with a
    live strength slider.  (The HAL's own HDR scene mode is a no-op.)
  * Capture Mode: Normal / Action (freeze motion).
  * Zebra overlay: stripes blown highlights (red) + crushed shadows (blue) on
    the preview; the EV slider snaps to neutral with a centre marker.
  * Video bitrate control and a steady-30 vs auto-5–30 frame-rate option.
  * Settings are mode-aware (only photo or video options shown), and the
    resolution pickers drop odd-aspect/encoder-padded sizes.
  * Background image writer for faster shot-to-shot; video-mode entry hardened
    so a stuck codec can't freeze the UI.
  * Faster auto-flash, a gentler ±2 EV brightness slider with a larger touch
    target, and a full Camera2 HAL capability dump tool (FC2_DUMP_CAPS).

 -- Sean Pollard <spollard08@gmail.com>  Fri, 20 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000

furicam2 (2.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial furicam2 release: camera driven through the Android Camera2 NDK via
    libhybris, replacing the QtMultimedia/gst-droid backend.
  * Photo capture (up to 21 MP) and 4K/HD H.264 video into MP4 with AAC audio.
  * WYSIWYG aspect ratios (4:3, 16:9, 1:1) with matching letterboxed preview.
  * Flash off/on/auto (auto emulated via AE-state metering on this HAL).
  * White balance presets, live QR scanning, macro/secondary cameras,
    front-camera mirror, tap-to-focus, pinch zoom.
  * HDR (OpenCV Mertens fusion) and GPS geotagging carried over.
  * Coexists with the original furicam, reusing its icon, GSettings schema,
    polkit rule and config.

 -- Sean Pollard <spollard08@gmail.com>  Wed, 18 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000
